    "serpentine": {
      // note": "Snake-kin (viper) — a fanged head + 3-segment body (fore/mid/hind, each flesh over its vertebrae) + tail. Venom is a real organ: the paired VENOM GLANDS behind the eyes carry the venom_bite, so destroying them takes the venomous strike with it (the fangs keep a plain bite). Snakes keep ONE functional lung (the right; the left is vestigial) and staggered kidneys (excretion → blood_filtration). No mammalian `spine` — the vertebrae ARE the skeleton.
      "parts": {
        "fangs"          : {"size": 14, "bleedRatio": 0.01, "hitWeight": 2, "weapons": ["bite"], "armor": 0.4},
