    "arachnid": {
      "// note": "Spider anatomy — a two-tagma body (prosoma/cephalothorax + opisthosoma) with arachnid-specific organs, NOT a borrowed mammal torso. The cephalothorax holds the synganglion (brain), 8 eyes, the paired VENOM GLANDS (which carry the venom_bite — destroy them and the bite goes dry, only a plain bite remains on the chelicerae), and the sucking stomach. The opisthosoma holds the tubular heart, paired book lungs, digestive gland (hepatopancreas), Malpighian tubules (excretion = kidney analog), and the SILK GLANDS / spinnerets ('thread sack'). Organ→capacity wiring is by pattern in PawnStatService (book lung → breathing, Malpighian → blood_filtration, etc). TODO: silk-gland health does not yet influence butcher silk-yield (butchering is recipe-based, not organ-aware) — wire it when butchering becomes per-organ.",
      "parts": {
        "cephalothorax"          : {"size": 55, "bleedRatio": 0.1, "hitWeight": 22, "armor": 1},
